    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-23T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-23T20:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/581</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-23T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7014. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 238. Embassy’s unnumbered telegram dated March 13, 11 a.m.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d129fn1">Not printed.</note> You may advise <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_OWH1">Owen</persName>, Stockholm, that it is
                    not practical for time being to operate with a white list. The next revised
                    edition of the United States enemy trading list, now in printers’ hands, will
                    contain names of firms with whom it is illegal to trade. It follows that trading
                    with all firms not on that list will be legal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
